meanings.definition: Not able to be determined or decided
meanings.sent1: The color of the sky was undeterminable due to the thick fog.
meanings.sent2: The outcome of the game was undeterminable until the final whistle.
meanings.sent3: It was undeterminable whether the cat or the dog made the mess in the living room.
meanings.sent4: The path through the dense forest was undeterminable, shrouded in mystery.
meanings.sent5: The true intentions of the mysterious stranger remained undeterminable.

meanings.sent1: The exact time of arrival was undeterminable due to traffic delays.
meanings.sent2: The value of the antique vase was undeterminable without an expert's opinion.
meanings.sent3: The number of stars in the sky seemed undeterminable on that clear night.
meanings.sent4: The depth of the ocean was undeterminable to the ancient sailors.
meanings.sent5: The complexity of the puzzle made the solution undeterminable at first glance.
